The paper deals with parameterizing hard combinatorial problems, which is a topic that falls under computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses algorithms for satisfiability problems, which are typically studied in the subfield of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper uses techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) to solve the problems. Finally, the paper explores how similar techniques can be used for vertex cover problems, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG).
